   307	
   308	### 4.10 Normalization
   309	
   310	Inbound normalization extracts these fields from a raw relay event:
   311	
   312	| Target field | Source | Fallback |
   313	|---|---|---|
   314	| `id` | `raw.messageId` or `raw.id` | Generated UUID |
   315	| `surfaceId` | Provided by relay (first arg to `receiveRaw`) | Error if missing |
   316	| `sessionId` | `raw.sessionId` or `raw.session?.id` | undefined |
   317	| `userId` | `raw.userId` or `raw.user?.id` or `raw.user` (if string) | **Error:** reject message and log error. `userId` is required. |
   318	| `workspaceId` | `raw.workspaceId` or `raw.workspace?.id` | `undefined` (optional) |
   319	| `text` | `raw.text` or `raw.content` or `raw.body` | Empty string; logs warning |
   320	| `receivedAt` | `raw.timestamp` or `raw.receivedAt` | `new Date().toISOString()` |
   321	| `raw` | Verbatim | Required |
   322	
   323	Normalization does not fail on missing optional fields; it logs warnings and uses fallbacks.
   324	
   325	> **Required field:** `userId` is required on `InboundMessage` (per core spec). If normalization cannot extract a user identifier from the raw payload, it must reject the message and log an error. It must not silently assign an anonymous ID without the product opting into that behavior via a custom `normalizationHook`.
